  <meta content="This test checks that a block element with 'contain: paint' establishes a new block formatting context which is independent and separate from others. This causes margin collapsing to be ineffective among vertically-adjacent boxes. In test, the bottom margin of the last in-flow child of boxes and bottom margin of their respective parent boxes do not collapse." name="assert">Test passes if there are 5 horizontal stripes across the page in this order (from top to bottom): an orange stripe, a blue stripe, a bright green stripe, a blue stripe and then an orange stripe.

